bug.short_desc: [abrt] mate-terminal: slowly_and_stupidly_obtain_timestamp(): mate-terminal killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Most of the mate apps crash if launched under gnome-wayland. This report was gfenerated on a fully updated clean fedora-workstation.
Version-Release number of selected component: mate-terminal-1.16.1-2.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: mate-terminal crash_function: slowly_and_stupidly_obtain_timestamp executable: /usr/bin/mate-terminal global_pid: 3058 kernel: 4.8.15-300.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (1 frames) #0 slowly_and_stupidly_obtain_timestamp at terminal.c:449
I noticed that these programs work correctly if forced to use xwayland with "env GDK_BACKEND=x11". May it be that they "try" to use wayland directly, given they're gtk3 apps and somehow do it wrong?
I suppose caja (and a few mate apps) have the same problem. Do I file a new bug?

Only if you find an application where i or other didn't fix it. Already done for https://github.com/mate-desktop/caja/commit/83ceaa5139036498533b941ac96b600e75bceff6 https://github.com/mate-desktop/atril/pull/237 https://github.com/mate-desktop/eom/pull/136 And please use github directly to file out reports + reporting it at rhbz. I am maintaining Mate alone here and forwarding issue which can only be fix by upstream is more and more an annoying extra work for me.
